<br>
My point was that the game is getting so easy that it's getting trivial and boring.  The only way to counteract that is to make things harder somehow to keep the game challenging and therefore interesting.  <br>
<br>
Improving NPC AI is in my opinion one of the better ways to do it, because the way to counter it is to use your brain and use tactics.  <br>
<br>
If they instead increased NPC hit points, AC, damage dealing, etc., that would make things more difficult too, but then your brainpower and tactics would make no difference.  I'd rather have the AI improvement, thanks.<br>
<br>
If getting to level 60 is trivial, what sense of accomplishment will you feel for having done it?  If it's that easy, all it means is that you put in the time.  Personally I feel more accomplishment after having done something that was difficult.<br>
<br>
I would also say that I really doubt this is going to universally make leveling harder.  There are plenty of areas with melee mobs to kill, and even among casters I imagine there will be plenty that still won't be that much harder than they were before.<br>
<br>
Also, as a Paladin, I suggest you take a minute to see how you could benefit from this in terms of the role you can play.  If an encounter is going to start off with a few mobs tossing Ice Comet at you, our Sanctification /disc just got another useful purpose--even if you can only use it once every 72 minutes, you might be able to break a camp that way where another class would have trouble doing so.  If stunning is more important to stop casters from casting, it will make Paladins much more popular in groups that want to camp caster heavy areas.<br>
<br>
In my opinion not only would this help the game overall, it also helps Paladins. <p><BR>
